p: More importantly, a number of dominant compounds in feijoa essential oil, including β-caryophyllene, humulene, β-elemene, α-cadinol, and linalool were discovered to harbor antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and anticancer activities [ 34, 35, 36, 37, 38], which indicates that feijoa essential oil could be bioactive and has the potential to be utilized in the pharmaceutical industry. Further investigations into the bioactivities of feijoa essential oil are, therefore, of great importance.
